.TH "fsl_esai_divisor_cal" 9 "fsl_esai_divisor_cal" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_esai_divisor_cal \- This function is used to calculate the divisors of psr, pm, fp and it is supposed to be called in set_dai_sysclk() and set_bclk().
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsl_esai_divisor_cal
.BI "(struct snd_soc_dai *dai "  ","
.BI "bool tx "  ","
.BI "u32 ratio "  ","
.BI "bool usefp "  ","
.BI "u32 fp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dai" 12
pointer to DAI
.IP "tx" 12
current setting is for playback or capture
.IP "ratio" 12
desired overall ratio for the paticipating dividers
.IP "usefp" 12
for HCK setting, there is no need to set fp divider
.IP "fp" 12
bypass other dividers by setting fp directly if fp != 0
